{{italic title}}
'''''The Abbreviacion of Statutis''''' (1519), of which fifteen editions appeared before 1625, is a book by [[John Rastell]]. It, and [[Termes de la Ley]], are the best known of his legal works.<ref>[[Encyclopædia Britannica Eleventh Edition]]. Cambridge University Press. 1911. Volume 22. [https://archive.org/stream/encyclopaediabri22chisrich#page/914/mode/1up Page 914]. "Rastell, John". Digital Copy from [[Internet Archive]].</ref>

It is said to be the first abridgement of the Statutes printed in English. It appears to be a translation with additions of the Abridgment des Statutes vieux.<ref>[[John Gage Marvin|Marvin, J. G.]], ''[[Marvin's Legal Bibliography|Legal bibliography, or a thesaurus of American, English, Irish and Scotch law books:together with some continental treatises]]''. T & J W Johnson. 1847.
[https://books.google.com/books?id=DSNEAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA599#v=onepage&q&f=false Page 599] from [[Google Books]].</ref>

